30:46.803 --> 30:48.597
<i>I'm going to go immediately</i>

30:48.597 --> 30:50.140
to my 5160 performance blade.

30:50.140 --> 30:51.266
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:51.266 --> 30:52.851
That's a happy billet.

30:52.851 --> 30:54.436
<i>So to assemble</i>
<i>my Damascus billet,</i>

30:54.436 --> 30:56.188
<i>I'm gonna do two billets,</i>

30:56.188 --> 30:58.356
and then I'm gonna weld
the two billets together.

30:58.356 --> 31:00.275
<i>I have my two billets,</i>

31:00.275 --> 31:01.318
<i>so I'm gonna let those</i>
<i>cool so I can</i>

31:01.318 --> 31:02.319
<i>get those two welded out.</i>

31:02.319 --> 31:03.445
So in the meantime,

31:03.445 --> 31:04.529
I'm gonna start to draw out

31:04.529 --> 31:06.073
<i>this big piece of 5160</i>

31:06.073 --> 31:07.991
<i>so my plan B will be ready.</i>

31:07.991 --> 31:10.077
[chuckles]

31:10.077 --> 31:12.162
So I'm gonna get them
in the fire

31:12.162 --> 31:13.914
and then back to forge-welding
temperature

31:13.914 --> 31:15.707
<i>and start drawing</i>
<i>it out again.</i>

31:15.707 --> 31:16.958
My God, that's a heavy billet.

31:16.958 --> 31:18.085
Come on, do what I tell you!

31:18.085 --> 31:19.753
<i>I'm physically exhausted.</i>

31:19.753 --> 31:20.962
<i>This big blade</i>
<i>is a pain in the ass.</i>

31:20.962 --> 31:22.547
<i>So it's the end of day one.</i>

31:22.547 --> 31:23.965
Instead of two billets,
I now have one.

31:23.965 --> 31:27.135
Um--oh!
And it's still really hot!

31:27.135 --> 31:28.845
Uh, I really hope that works.

31:28.845 --> 31:31.264
I really don't want to
have to use this 5160.

31:31.264 --> 31:33.141
But, uh, I'm gonna prepare
for it anyway.

31:33.141 --> 31:35.519
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:35.519 --> 31:38.021
<i>- This is day one</i>
<i>of the nodachi.</i>

31:38.021 --> 31:39.981
<i>Big weapon.</i>

31:39.981 --> 31:41.233
I purposefully ordered steel

31:41.233 --> 31:42.776
<i>closer to the parameters of</i>

31:42.776 --> 31:44.694
<i>a general-sized blade,</i>

31:44.694 --> 31:47.572
so I felt very relaxed
and very confident

31:47.572 --> 31:50.158
that I was gonna save myself
a lot of physical abuse.

31:50.158 --> 31:51.493
[chuckles]

31:51.493 --> 31:53.286
We're an hour 45
into the build.

31:53.286 --> 31:56.123
And that, my friends,
is a crack.

31:56.123 --> 31:57.833
It's cause to start again.

31:57.833 --> 31:59.251
There's no reason to panic.

31:59.251 --> 32:01.128
<i>This is just day one.</i>

32:01.128 --> 32:03.296
<i>Good night's sleep,</i>
<i>couple of beers,</i>

32:03.296 --> 32:05.507
and I'll be good to go
tomorrow morning.

32:05.507 --> 32:08.176
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:08.176 --> 32:10.178
<i>- So I'm hoping my billet</i>
<i>is together.</i>

32:10.178 --> 32:12.430
I'm gonna grind it
and check my welds today.

32:12.430 --> 32:15.350
<i>I'm never really</i>
<i>completely, uh,</i>

32:15.350 --> 32:16.685
sure that it's gonna weld

32:16.685 --> 32:17.811
until I get
my first grind done.

32:17.811 --> 32:20.647
[machine whirring]

32:23.942 --> 32:25.318
<i>[dramatic musical flair]</i>

32:25.318 --> 32:29.823
Ah, [bleep].

32:29.823 --> 32:31.158
- Ah, [bleep].

32:31.158 --> 32:32.325
<i>I have a failure.</i>

32:32.325 --> 32:34.411
I have a delamination.

32:34.411 --> 32:35.912
<i>For me, this is too great</i>
<i>of a chance</i>

32:35.912 --> 32:37.664
<i>that my blade might fail.</i>

32:37.664 --> 32:39.916
Losing my Damascus billet
is a little disappointing.

32:39.916 --> 32:42.169
Um...but it's not
the end of the world.

32:42.169 --> 32:44.087
<i>That's why I have a plan B.</i>

32:44.087 --> 32:45.797
<i>So instead of turning in</i>
<i>something that's gonna fail,</i>

32:45.797 --> 32:47.841
I would rather turn in
something that's gonna be--

32:47.841 --> 32:49.593
it's not quite as pretty,

32:49.593 --> 32:51.553
<i>but it will perform much,</i>
<i>much better.</i>

32:51.553 --> 32:53.930
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:53.930 --> 32:55.140
<i>- It's day three,</i>

32:55.140 --> 32:57.058
and all the hard work is done.

32:57.058 --> 33:00.020
So today, I'm gonna
set my radius,

33:00.020 --> 33:02.063
<i>which is the curve</i>
<i>of the blade.</i>

33:02.063 --> 33:04.816
<i>I set up a bending jig</i>
<i>in my vice</i>

33:04.816 --> 33:06.693
and use the leverage
of the blade itself,

33:06.693 --> 33:08.904
<i>lay a little bend in there</i>

33:08.904 --> 33:10.780
<i>all the way around.</i>

33:10.780 --> 33:12.115
I'm a modern metalworker.

33:12.115 --> 33:14.159
<i>We do what's necessary.</i>

33:14.159 --> 33:15.994
Next is the quench.

33:15.994 --> 33:18.371
The most difficult part was
to heat the blade.

33:18.371 --> 33:20.040
<i>It's a long blade.</i>

33:20.040 --> 33:21.374
<i>A blade that long,</i>

33:21.374 --> 33:23.084
it's gonna want to travel.

33:23.084 --> 33:24.127
<i>The little warps,</i>
<i>they're gonna happen.</i>

33:24.127 --> 33:25.754
Hot steel!

33:25.754 --> 33:27.589
<i>The quench is</i>
<i>the make-or-break moment</i>

33:27.589 --> 33:29.174
<i>for the blade.</i>

33:29.174 --> 33:31.009
<i>This is when</i>
<i>that hunk of steel</i>

33:31.009 --> 33:32.719
<i>becomes a weapon.</i>

33:32.719 --> 33:34.221
<i>And, uh,</i>

33:34.221 --> 33:36.223
things have to be just right.

33:36.223 --> 33:37.682
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:37.682 --> 33:38.808
<i>The file skates.</i>

33:38.808 --> 33:40.810
Hopefully, it's hard enough

33:40.810 --> 33:43.230
for whatever they're gonna
bash that thing against

33:43.230 --> 33:44.272
<i>and hold its edge.</i>

33:44.272 --> 33:45.982
All right.

33:45.982 --> 33:48.026
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:48.026 --> 33:49.319
<i>- So today, I just fit</i>
<i>the tsuba to the sword...</i>

33:49.319 --> 33:50.737
Super happy.

33:50.737 --> 33:52.489
Everything went just
as planned.

33:52.489 --> 33:55.367
<i>...and, uh, get</i>
<i>my handle made.</i>

33:55.367 --> 33:57.994
<i>I'm gonna use poplar</i>
<i>for the handle.</i>

33:57.994 --> 34:00.080
<i>So the two pieces of wood,</i>
<i>milled out,</i>

34:00.080 --> 34:01.831
they fit perfectly
around the tang.

34:01.831 --> 34:03.750
[laughing] That's a big sword.

34:03.750 --> 34:05.168
I'm gonna glue this together

34:05.168 --> 34:07.629
now that I know it all
fits up nicely.

34:07.629 --> 34:09.631
<i>While I'm epoxying</i>
<i>my handle together,</i>

34:09.631 --> 34:11.758
<i>I get a little overzealous</i>
<i>with my clamps...</i>

34:11.758 --> 34:13.843
[bleep]

34:13.843 --> 34:15.845
And I crack my handle.

34:15.845 --> 34:18.473
That sucks so much.

34:18.473 --> 34:20.350
So I got a big crack

34:20.350 --> 34:22.519
right here
in the side of my wood.

34:22.519 --> 34:24.437
So I'm gonna squeeze some epoxy

34:24.437 --> 34:26.481
in this crack, and hopefully
it'll be okay.

34:26.481 --> 34:28.483
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:28.483 --> 34:31.236
Traditionally, the nodachi
are wrapped in a ray skin.

34:31.236 --> 34:33.613
<i>It has a great texture--</i>
<i>gives it great grip.</i>

34:33.613 --> 34:35.198
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:35.198 --> 34:37.200
<i>I basically have</i>
<i>all the components</i>

34:37.200 --> 34:39.035
<i>of my nodachi finished.</i>

34:39.035 --> 34:40.912
Yeah, that's gonna be
a big sword.

34:40.912 --> 34:42.580
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:42.580 --> 34:43.707
- It's day five,

34:43.707 --> 34:44.958
<i>and what I have left is</i>

34:44.958 --> 34:46.668
<i>the handle construction.</i>

34:46.668 --> 34:48.044
Having never done

34:48.044 --> 34:49.421
anything like this before,

34:49.421 --> 34:51.006
um, I'm kinda winging it.

34:51.006 --> 34:53.258
<i>I'm going by intuition.</i>

34:53.258 --> 34:55.135
I'm worried about
not having enough.

34:55.135 --> 34:57.762
Hopefully it's good enough.

34:57.762 --> 35:00.140
The wrap I did for my wakizashi

35:00.140 --> 35:02.601
in The Forge, it was rather
aggressive

35:02.601 --> 35:03.977
and the judges didn't like it.

35:03.977 --> 35:05.604
It hurt their dainty hands.

35:05.604 --> 35:08.773
So I made this one
to accommodate their...

35:08.773 --> 35:10.358
their soft hands.

35:10.358 --> 35:13.069
<i>[tranquil music]</i>

35:13.069 --> 35:14.571
- Nicholas, Dave,

35:14.571 --> 35:16.406
welcome back to The Forge
once again.

35:16.406 --> 35:18.366
This has been a long road
for you guys.

35:18.366 --> 35:20.243
You knocked out the farriers,

35:20.243 --> 35:21.745
you knocked out
the blacksmiths,

35:21.745 --> 35:23.163
and now we've got an armorer

35:23.163 --> 35:24.164
and a modern metalworker

35:24.164 --> 35:25.582
jockeying for the title

35:25.582 --> 35:27.375
of "Forged in Fire"
tournament champion.

35:27.375 --> 35:29.044
Your nodachis look fantastic.

35:29.044 --> 35:30.378
Nicholas, how did it go
for you?

35:30.378 --> 35:32.339
- This is the hardest, uh,

35:32.339 --> 35:34.049
sword build I've ever
had to do.

35:34.049 --> 35:36.551
<i>I went with 5160</i>
<i>for the blade.</i>

35:36.551 --> 35:38.261
<i>The tsuba is made from</i>
<i>cold-rolled steel.</i>

35:38.261 --> 35:40.639
<i>Two of the ornamentations</i>
<i>on the handle</i>

35:40.639 --> 35:42.974
<i>are 16th-century Edo period</i>

35:42.974 --> 35:45.226
from an original katana.

35:45.226 --> 35:48.313
- Dave, please tell us
that you have a blade

35:48.313 --> 35:49.981
that is as competitive
as Nick's.

35:49.981 --> 35:51.983
- Well, I can hope.
- [laughs]

35:51.983 --> 35:54.486
<i>- My blade also is 5160</i>
<i>tool steel.</i>

35:54.486 --> 35:56.738
<i>A solid copper habaki</i>
<i>construction.</i>

35:56.738 --> 35:58.490
<i>The handle is poplar wood</i>

35:58.490 --> 36:00.825
<i>with a linen</i>
<i>and paracord wrap.</i>

36:00.825 --> 36:02.661
- Well, gentlemen,

36:02.661 --> 36:03.703
your blades will now
be put through

36:03.703 --> 36:05.121
a series of three tests,

36:05.121 --> 36:06.831
and up first, the kill test.

36:06.831 --> 36:07.874
Doug?

36:07.874 --> 36:09.834
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

36:09.834 --> 36:11.378
- All right, weaponsmiths.

36:11.378 --> 36:12.921
I will take your nodachi

36:12.921 --> 36:15.382
and cut this pig up
in different sections

36:15.382 --> 36:17.092
until I run out of pig.

36:17.092 --> 36:17.967
All right, Nicholas,
you're up first.

36:17.967 --> 36:19.135
You ready?

36:19.135 --> 36:20.220
- I'm ready, let's do this.

36:20.220 --> 36:21.763
<i>Of course I'm nervous.</i>

36:21.763 --> 36:23.431
<i>There's a lot</i>
<i>on the line today.</i>

36:23.431 --> 36:25.517
I really just hope
my sword performs.

36:25.517 --> 36:27.102
I really hope I don't get
a failure.

36:27.102 --> 36:28.728
<i>I hope it doesn't break</i>
<i>or bend.</i>

36:28.728 --> 36:33.233
<i>[dramatic musical buildup]</i>

36:33.233 --> 36:34.818
<i>[rock music]</i>

36:34.818 --> 36:36.486
Nice.

36:36.486 --> 36:43.076
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:43.076 --> 36:44.661
- It'll kill.

36:44.661 --> 36:46.121
[both laughing]
- That was crazy.

36:46.121 --> 36:47.122
- All right, Nicholas.

36:47.122 --> 36:48.456
It is a very sharp blade

36:48.456 --> 36:49.958
with a nice weight
to maneuver with it

36:49.958 --> 36:52.001
because of the
lightness that you have.

36:52.001 --> 36:53.837
The handle construction
is beautiful.

36:53.837 --> 36:55.588
The only thing that
I was worried about

36:55.588 --> 36:57.298
were the pins that
you have in here.

36:57.298 --> 36:58.508
They're protruding.

36:58.508 --> 36:59.926
But most importantly,

36:59.926 --> 37:01.428
it will kill.

37:01.428 --> 37:02.929
- Nice.

37:02.929 --> 37:04.222
- All right, Dave,
it's your turn.

37:04.222 --> 37:05.432
You ready?
- Yes, sir.

37:05.432 --> 37:06.558
<i>[tense musical flair]</i>

37:06.558 --> 37:07.851
- Here we go.

37:07.851 --> 37:10.311
<i>[quiet musical buildup]</i>

37:10.311 --> 37:13.398
<i>[rock music]</i>

37:13.398 --> 37:20.363
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:21.448 --> 37:22.782
- Hmm, it's not as sharp
as yours.

37:22.782 --> 37:23.783
- Dave,

37:23.783 --> 37:24.784
the weight of the blade

37:24.784 --> 37:25.910
is a little bit forward

37:25.910 --> 37:27.662
for me to be very accurate

37:27.662 --> 37:29.247
on every strike.

37:29.247 --> 37:32.959
But anything that this blade
touches and cuts,

37:32.959 --> 37:34.377
it will kill.

37:34.377 --> 37:36.296
- Thank you, sir.

37:36.296 --> 37:38.006
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:38.006 --> 37:39.841
- Hello, gents.

37:39.841 --> 37:41.676
Welcome to the pole and the pot
smash and chop.

37:41.676 --> 37:44.345
To test the strength
and durability of your edge,

37:44.345 --> 37:46.306
as well as the overall
construction of your nodachis,

37:46.306 --> 37:48.475
I'm gonna be chopping away
at these poles

37:48.475 --> 37:50.310
and then I'm gonna take aim
at these pots.

37:50.310 --> 37:51.770
Nicholas, you're up first.
Are you ready?

37:51.770 --> 37:54.147
- I'm ready.
Let's do it.

37:54.147 --> 37:56.065
<i>[dramatic musical flair]</i>

37:56.065 --> 37:57.734
<i>[intense musical buildup]</i>

37:57.734 --> 38:00.737
<i>[rock music]</i>

38:00.737 --> 38:07.619
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:12.081 --> 38:14.709
[pot shattering]

38:14.709 --> 38:15.835
- Well, Nick,
first things first,

38:15.835 --> 38:17.629
this thing is amazing to swing.

38:17.629 --> 38:18.922
I get the feeling like I could

38:18.922 --> 38:20.799
cleave armies with this thing.

38:20.799 --> 38:21.966
That being said,

38:21.966 --> 38:23.676
right here near the tip,

38:23.676 --> 38:25.804
there's a pretty
significant roll

38:25.804 --> 38:27.263
You can hear it.
[metal pings]

38:27.263 --> 38:29.474
These pins that are
sticking out pretty proud,

38:29.474 --> 38:31.434
they kind of bit into my
fingers as I was swinging it.

38:31.434 --> 38:32.936
But well done.

38:32.936 --> 38:34.270
- Thank you.

38:34.270 --> 38:35.563
- [chuckling]

38:35.563 --> 38:36.773
- Dave, you're up.
You ready?

38:36.773 --> 38:38.107
- Yes, sir.
- All right.

38:38.107 --> 38:39.943
<i>- In a blade this long,</i>

38:39.943 --> 38:41.694
<i>there's so much that can</i>
<i>go wrong.</i>

38:41.694 --> 38:43.905
You just don't know until
the judges start working it.

38:43.905 --> 38:45.406
<i>[intense musical buildup]</i>

38:45.406 --> 38:48.451
<i>[rock music]</i>

38:48.451 --> 38:55.208
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:02.423 --> 39:04.801
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

39:04.801 --> 39:06.469
- Well, Dave,

39:06.469 --> 39:08.304
your edge held up pretty well.

39:08.304 --> 39:11.891
There's a little dulling,
but no big deflections.

39:11.891 --> 39:13.393
The handle is comfortable.

39:13.393 --> 39:15.979
Well done.
- Thank you, sir.

39:15.979 --> 39:18.314
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:18.314 --> 39:19.691
- All right, gentlemen.

39:19.691 --> 39:21.192
It's time for
the sharpness test.

39:21.192 --> 39:23.403
Now, in this test,
we've decided to

39:23.403 --> 39:26.447
scale up the water bottles
to the size of the nodachi.

39:26.447 --> 39:28.658
A sharp blade should pass
right through them.

39:28.658 --> 39:30.785
A dull blade or a chipped blade

39:30.785 --> 39:33.454
might catch them, push them,
tear them up.

39:33.454 --> 39:34.831
We're gonna find out.

39:34.831 --> 39:36.082
Nicholas, you're up.
Are you ready?

39:36.082 --> 39:37.876
- I'm ready.

39:37.876 --> 39:43.965
<i>This is nerve-wracking.</i>
<i>It's a nail-biter.</i>

39:43.965 --> 39:46.301
- You can't tell I'm nervous,
scared, and excited?

39:46.301 --> 39:48.011
<i>I don't know what to think.</i>

39:48.011 --> 39:49.762
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:49.762 --> 39:52.682
<i>[rock music]</i>

39:52.682 --> 39:54.601
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:54.601 --> 39:56.269
Nice.

39:56.269 --> 39:59.230
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

39:59.230 --> 40:01.482
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:01.482 --> 40:04.235
- Nicholas, your blade
is remarkably light.

40:04.235 --> 40:07.155
Um, your balance on this blade

40:07.155 --> 40:08.281
is great.

40:08.281 --> 40:09.490
Nicely done on this weapon.

40:09.490 --> 40:10.408
- Thank you.
- Well done.

40:10.408 --> 40:11.409
It's a very sharp blade.

40:11.409 --> 40:12.577
All right, Dave.

40:12.577 --> 40:13.620
You're up.
Are you ready?

40:13.620 --> 40:15.663
- I'm ready.
- Okay.

40:15.663 --> 40:17.624
<i>- It's like a roller coaster</i>
<i>ride right now.</i>

40:17.624 --> 40:19.834
I'm up and I'm nervous,

40:19.834 --> 40:21.711
<i>and I'm calm,</i>
<i>then I'm nervous.</i>

40:21.711 --> 40:23.421
And I'm like back and forth,
back and forth.

40:23.421 --> 40:26.382
<i>[heavy guitar buildup]</i>

40:26.382 --> 40:29.302
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

40:29.302 --> 40:32.680
[chuckling]

40:32.680 --> 40:34.349
It's sharp.

40:34.349 --> 40:37.226
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

40:37.226 --> 40:39.187
Okay.

40:39.187 --> 40:40.730
- All right, Dave.

40:40.730 --> 40:42.941
Your handle construction:
super comfortable.

40:42.941 --> 40:45.485
I like the size of it.
It felt really good.

40:45.485 --> 40:47.528
Overall, it's sharp.

40:47.528 --> 40:49.364
Good job.
- Thank you, sir.

40:49.364 --> 40:51.324
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:51.324 --> 40:52.408
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

40:52.408 --> 40:53.534
- Bladesmiths,

40:53.534 --> 40:55.203
this tournament of champions

40:55.203 --> 40:57.372
has been an
extraordinary competition

40:57.372 --> 40:59.374
in weaponsmithing.

40:59.374 --> 41:01.167
But the judges' deliberation
is complete,

41:01.167 --> 41:03.002
and they've made their
final decision.

41:03.002 --> 41:05.463
Only one of you can be
our champion.

41:05.463 --> 41:08.716
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:08.716 --> 41:09.926
Dave.

41:09.926 --> 41:11.719
Congratulations,

41:11.719 --> 41:14.889
you are the "Forged in Fire"
tournament champion.

41:14.889 --> 41:16.057
Nicholas, I want you to know

41:16.057 --> 41:17.767
there has been no finer margin

41:17.767 --> 41:19.727
by which we've declared
a champion.

41:19.727 --> 41:21.229
You did the armorers proud.

41:21.229 --> 41:22.730
Unfortunately,

41:22.730 --> 41:25.024
your blade didn't make the cut.

