your nodachi.

41:37.912 --> 41:39.956
<i>- I'm really proud</i>
<i>of the weapon that I made.</i>

41:39.956 --> 41:41.749
<i>It never feels good to lose.</i>

41:41.749 --> 41:44.794
<i>But I enjoyed myself immensely</i>

41:44.794 --> 41:46.838
through all of the stress,
through all of the drama.

41:46.838 --> 41:48.798
<i>I came to represent</i>
<i>the armorers class,</i>

41:48.798 --> 41:50.466
<i>and I think I did</i>
<i>a good job of that.</i>

41:50.466 --> 41:52.719
<i>I hope my brothers</i>
<i>are proud of me.</i>

41:52.719 --> 41:54.804
- Dave, congratulations.

41:54.804 --> 41:57.306
You are the "Forged in Fire"
tournament champion,

41:57.306 --> 41:59.100
beating out
15 other competitors

41:59.100 --> 42:00.935
to win our biggest prize ever:

42:00.935 --> 42:03.646
$50,000.

42:03.646 --> 42:05.648
And you look like a badass
with that weapon right now.

42:05.648 --> 42:07.567
- [laughing]

42:07.567 --> 42:10.695
- Dave, please present
your nodachi to the judges.

42:10.695 --> 42:13.114
<i>- I believe I've done</i>
<i>the modern metalworkers proud.</i>

42:13.114 --> 42:15.491
<i>The skill level</i>
<i>with this last competition</i>

42:15.491 --> 42:17.452
was off the charts.

42:17.452 --> 42:18.995
<i>My name's Dave Parthemore,</i>

42:18.995 --> 42:23.124
